comments.body:
I think that passing fieldViewBuilder, focusNode, and textEditingController is a valid use case, like if you want to listen to them or do something special to them above the RawAutocomplete.  See the example below.

This line 445 just makes sure that you don't pass one without the other.  The assert on line 438 doesn't cover that case.  I suppose RawAutocomplete could create the one that you didn't pass in for you, but it seems unusual that you'd want to do that.

```dart
late TextEditingController controller;
late FocusNode node;

void initState() {
  super.initState();
  node = FocusNode();
  node.addListener(() {
    // ... Do some thing special with the FocusNode.
  });
  controller = TextEditingController();
  controller.addListener(() {
    // ... Do some thing special with the controller.
  });
}

Widget build(BuildContext context) {
  return RawAutocomplete(
    textEditingController: controller,
    focusNode: node,
    fieldViewBuilder: (BuildContext context, TextEditingController textEditingController, FocusNode focusNode, VoidCallback onFieldSubmitted) {
     // node and controller are equivalent to focusNode and textEditingController here.
      return TextField(
        controller: textEditingController,
        focusNode: focusNode,
      );
    }
  );
}
```

